        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>April 11th 1849</date>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Revd. I. Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours of the <date>9th</date> inst: is<lb/> received, and we send
                you herewith the goods you<lb/> write us for. Of the Blue &amp; white satin we send
                you<lb/> eighteen yards, which you say is what will be required.<lb/> We do not
                think it worth while to send the whole<lb/> piece as it contains over a hundred
                yards. Should<lb/> you need more we can forward it at once.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The piece of white figured silk contains 7 Â¾ yards,<lb/> which is
                all we have of the same on hand at present,<lb/> we can however import it for you,
                if you wish.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We send you all we have of the crimson &amp; gold<lb/> Brocatelle.
                There are two pieces together, the one piece<lb/> containing 11 9/16 yds and the
                other 4 Â½ yds: Please<lb/> cut from the shorter piece <hi rend="underline"
                    >first</hi>. Should you have<lb/> any of the crimson &amp; gold Brocatelle left
                which you<lb/> wish to return, please return it within a week, as<lb/> we may have a
                chance to dispose of it within that<lb/> time, having no more of the same in
                store.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In reference to <hi rend="underline">single width</hi> Brocatelles,
                we can<lb/> offer them to you at from 2.25 to 2.40 per yard,<lb/> the same as you
                can purchase from <persName>Mr Levy</persName> at 2.62 Â½<lb/> should you require any
                more of the crimson &amp; gold Brocatelle<lb/> we can send it to you soon as we are
                constantly re=<lb/>=ceiving those styles of goods in store, though we have</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>no more of the same kind at present.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We shall be happy to hear from you at all<lb/> times. Believe us Dr
                Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Your obt servts</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Solomon &amp; Hart</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <placeName>242 Broadway</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">pr <add>?</add></p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
